Hungary Focusing on Debt, Deficit Reductions in 2012, Simor Says

-- B y   A g n e s   L o v a s z
-- 
2011-10-06T10:38:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-06/hungary-focusing-on-debt-deficit-reductions-in-2012-simor-says.html
Hungary’s government is embarking on
a tightening of budget policy in 2012 with a focus on reducing
the debt and deficit levels, central bank President Andras Simor
said.  “The government is acutely aware that debt needs to be
brought down and budget policy needs to be extremely
disciplined,” Simor said in a speech in  London  today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Agnes Lovasz in London at 
 alovasz@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Zoltan Simon at 
 zsimon@bloomberg.net  